title: For Sale:  SWR Spectre II  .22 caliber suppressor
postcontent:
SPECTRE II

THE DURABLE SUPPRESSOR

With its construction of ultra high performance and tough Stainless Steel, the Spectre II allows weapon fire to go virtually unnoticed. It is not only super tough, but also one of the quietest 22 suppressor known to man. With the Spectre II, users will also enjoy its multi-caliber versatility.

CLICK TOGETHER ASSEMBLY (CTA) BAFFLE STACK

The Spectre II has a unique CTA baffle design for easy disassembly and is user serviceable, which is very important for any .22 lr silencer. Because the .22 lr round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue .22 silencers must be able to be disassembled for cleaning and regularly maintained. Most .22 silencers on the market can be disassembled for cleaning, however they require cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds or often times they will fuse together and they are unable to come apart. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the silencer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the tube, there is simply too much build up of fouling and lead to remove the tube from most .22 lr silencers on the market. The Spectre II has the unique CTA baffle design that keeps the carbon and lead debris from reaching the silencer tube allowing it to be disassembled easily.

title: For Sale:  Silencerco Osprey .45.  Black in color!
postcontent:
With the modern combat handgun in mind, Silencerco set out to create a silencer that performs well and looks like it belongs—the best possible marriage between host weapon and silencer. Silencerco went to work to make a suppressor that maximizes sound suppression levels, allows the use of more host pistols with factory sights, and has more operationally friendly features. What was created was the Osprey pistol silencer available for 9mm, .40 S&W, and 45ACP.


The Osprey is an eccentric silencer, which means that the bore does not run down the middle of the tube. Because of this eccentric design, most of the baffles and internal volume is beneath the centerline of the bore and out of the way of the gun’s sights, thus leaving the shooter the ability to use factory sights with little or no sight or target obstruction. The Osprey has flat side walls and angled edges that mimic many modern combat handgun slides and is just slightly wider than most host pistols. This feature allows the host weapon to be holstered with many popular open bottom holster designs with Osprey attached. The Osprey contains approximately 30% more internal volume than a traditional round tube silencer at the same length, but does so without obscuring the shooter’s sight picture or adding excessive width and length.

title: For Sale:  Like New RED JACKET AK 47
location: NW San Antonio, San Antonio, Texas
postcontent:
Assembled by Red Jacket firearms in Baton Rouge, LA. Yugoslavian M92 parts kit and a no dak spud receiver to make this impressive firearm.

Please note, this gun is used but in immaculate condition. This gun has had 60 rounds through it since Red Jacket built it. 

One of the things that makes this firearm so incredibly unique is the fact that the original Yugoslavian military issue barrel was utilized. The United States Department of Defense no longer allows the import of functioning barrels to be included with parts kits imported into the U.S. Barrels made in the U.S. are offered and often included with parts kits like these - the trouble is that the U.S. made barrels pale in comparison to a military-issue quality barrel.

Since the factory barrel was used, the previous owner had Red Jacket pin their inert silencer onto the muzzle of the firearm, thus making it NFA compliant. Due to that, this gun transfers to a regular FFL and no $200 tax stamp is needed as it is not considered an SBR (short barrel rifle). The inert silencer does not actually silence the sound. It is a dummy silencer. It's purpose is to extend the barrel, and it looks really cool.

This rifle has 1 magazine that comes with it. I am asking $3,000 or best offer. I am on the fence about selling this gun, and not in a hurry to do so.

title: For Sale:  Ottoman Empire(Turkish)Military Snider/Springfield
postcontent: Very scarce Ottoman Empire (Turkish) military Snider/Springfield breech loading rifle. Caliber: .577, rimmed. This was originally a US Springfield percussion muzzle-loading rifle. Many Springfield rifles were sold to France during the Franco-Prussian War. The Prussians captured many such rifles and eventually sold them to the Ottoman Empire after the war ended. The Ottoman Empire also purchased many Springfield muzzle-loaders directly in the USA. All of these Springfields were eventually converted to Snider breech loading rifles. The conversions were done in English, Belgian a and Turkish arsenals. The Snider actions were purchased in England, Belgium, or manufactured locally in Turkey. This particular rifle features a US manufactured lockplate, stock and buttplate. The lockplate still displays original US markings, "U.S. Springfield, 1859, American Eagle

title: For Sale:  Refinshed AK wood stock set. These were on rifles carried by real soldiers in real conflict zones in SE Europe. Real battle scars.
postcontent:
Own a piece of AK 47 history! These stocks were used on rifles carried by soldiers and rebels in the border conflicts and ethnic cleansing conflicts in Turkey, Yugoslavia, and Bosnia-Herzegovina. They show signs of what they have been through. One set has some carving on it that might be a name of a loved one or fallen comrade. The other has "ALLAHU EKBER" carved on the side of the upper handguard. After some research I found that  the Allahu Ekber mountain range is a range in northern Turkey where several Ottoman soldiers froze to death during a march through the mountains in World War 1. And the Turkish military still honors their death and sacrifice to this day.

These sets have been cleaned up, stained and given a protective coat of polyurethane to preserve the history carved and beaten into the wood and now looks great.

This set is for AKM models and includes upper and lower handguards and buttstock for a stamped reciever. The stock has a sling swivel and steel buttplate with trapdoor for buttstock cleaning kit. And i can throw in a plastic or bakelite pistol grip for $5 if you want.

title: For Sale:  SURPLUS ASSAULT RUSSIAN SEMI AUTO 1941 SVT40 7.62X54R 10 DETACHABLE MAG FAIR/GOOD CONDITION
location: Lexington, South Carolina, Columbia, South Carolina
postcontent:
Very rare hard to find (1941) RUSSIAN SVT-40 RIFLE - 7.62x54r caliber semi-automatic rifle. 10 round detachable magazine. The Samozaryadnaya Vintovka Tokareva (SVT-40) was designed by Soviet Arms Designer Fedor Tokarev. It was manufactured between 1941 and 1945. The SVT-40 is an improved and simplified rifle design over the SVT-38. 
During WWII SVT-40 rifles were highly prized captures by both German and Finnish troops. Many pictures in books of German troops on the eastern front carrying the SVT-40. 
The biggest issue with the SVT 40 is the ejection of the spent casing due to improper gas cartridge adjustment and improper powder loads. DO NOT use any loads over 150 grain as this will destroy the gas chamber. Overall condition is rated as fair to good for an old surplus military rifle that will never be imported again into the USA. 10 magazine is an aftermarket so not all original, all other numbers match. Wood stock has 2 cracks/splits at rear top and at mag well. Gun has some surface rust spots. I would grade gun as fair to good condition. Still has blueing on metal parts. Additional pictures could be emailed to serious buyers only!! If must be shipped, I will only ship to an FFL Licensed Holder Dealer Only!! Great for shooting , collecting or the one that got away! Serious Inquiries Only Please!!! These will never be imported again so no B.S., will just place back into the safe where the value is only going up still. If buying local in state, I will need a copy of your state photo I.D. and disclaimer as proof of sale. Many Thanks.
